<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Parch" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Parch,</orth> 1) tr. to scorch, to dry: <cit><quote>--ing heat,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1145" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1145</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.77" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.81" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 81</bibl>. <cit><quote>--ed lips,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.7.40" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 7, 40</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>hath thy fiery heart so --ed thine entrails,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.87" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 87</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>impasted with the --ing streets,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.481" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 481</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) intr. to be scorched: <cit><quote>p. in Afric sun,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.370" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 370</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>